                  </hi>. I am a widow and live in Caroline-street, Greenwich. I was standing on Greenwich-hill on the 24th of March, in the afternoon—I had a purse with four sixpences and a farthing in it—I had 3<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. in coppers—this is my purse. <hi rend="smallCaps">JOHN CARPENTER</hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable R</hi> 84.) I was on duty—I saw the two prisoners on the hill—I saw them go behind several females, and each of them try several pockets—I then saw Penton go behind Mrs. Gleaves—Lopaz was behind Penton, with his hands in his pockets, spreading out, and covering him—I then saw Penton lift up Mrs. Gleaves' dress, put his hand into her pocket, and take out this purse—I caught his hand—he dropped the purse, but I caught one farthing in his hand.</p>
